post_text:
Welcome back to another school year!

The Pto is always looking for more members!
Please know that we also love Grandmas, Grandpas, Aunts and Uncles. Anyone in your child's life that would like to help support his or her school, is welcome to join! You might want to come to all the meetings or you might not, that is up to you. You might just want to volunteer here or there or maybe donate to an event. No matter how you see yourself serving in the PTO please let us know! You can message us here on Facebook or come to our first meeting at the school library on September 14th at 5:15. We hope to see you there!

post_text: We are planning a lock-in for grades K-6 on Friday, November 8th. Please let us know by Friday, November 1st if your child will be attending. Forms were given out at parent teacher conferences. Additional forms may be picked up in the school office. There will be pizza, games, crafts, movies, and more. We hope to see your child there! It's that time of year again that we are asking for donations for the Chilhowee Carnival! We have delivered or mailed out over 200 request letters and filled out lots of online requests! Anyone that wants to donate can send me a msg and i can give you the info on where to send your donation or arrange to pick it up. The PTO provides money for field trips, playground equipment, class room supplies, technology updates and other educational materials to enhance our children‚Äôs education. We hold several events throughout the year including a holiday shop, bingo, a school carnival and silent auction, and other fun family events to raise funds for these activities and supplies.
Thank You to all that help us provide for our small school by participating in the fundraisers & donating!

post_text: Don't forget City Wide Clean up is April 7th and 8th. Please start gathering your unwanted items, trash, and yard debris. You can either take it up and put it in the dumpster behind City Hall starting Friday afternoon or you can place it on the curb for our volunteers to pick up for you. If you are in need of large trash bags you may pick them up at the Corner Store. If you are in need of help please contact the Corner Store we have high school kids in need of community service hours that can come and help you all throughout this week.

post_text: Phase 1 is complete. The area for the new equipment is ready! Thanks to the heavy equipment and work from the Lowe family it didn't take long. We also removed the old kickball backstop, and a tree from out front. Instalation is the week of November 28th, we will then come back on December 3rd to replace the boarder around the area and put the gravel back around the new equipment. Volunteers will be needed on December 3.

post_text: PTO is happy to announce that, we are working tomorrow to remove some of the old unusable equipment on the playground in the morning. This is to prepare the space for the new equipment we purchased that is scheduled to be installed the week of the 28th. This is very exciting for us and the kids can't wait to see what they will soon get to play on outside! We will be posting pictures as our project gets underway!
